commit fbee9dd9e4ac37919959dee5c5437bea376f1f66
Author: Aaron Montgomery <aaronpmontgomery@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Feb 27 12:24:09 2026 -1000

    fix(scheduling): align DB day_of_week mapping with python datetime standard and unblock solver

    This commit resolves critical off-by-one bugs in how faculty weekly templates and schedule preferences map to calendar days. The database has been shifted from Sunday=0 to Monday=0 to align perfectly with Python's date.weekday() standard. Additionally, the FacultySupervision constraint has been degraded to a SoftConstraint to prevent the solver from crashing when faculty vacation forces unavoidable supervision gaps. Includes a new script to dynamically generate a Constraints Registry.

